    <note>Li(2) Suzhi [1086] Di's [1096] nephew, Chengzhi's [978] elder brother and Huizhi's [1036] and Dongzhi's [1104] cousin, Xiaochun's [1028] father. His eldest and youngest daughters became buddhist nuns (religious names cited). Father-in-law of Zhang(1) Kui's [250] nephew, Zhang(1) Xu [3146], and Han(1) Zhen [3323], the son of Yang(2) Tuo's [2028] daughter. Her elder sister was the first wife of Zhen's father (sororate) and mother of Han(1) Duo [655]. Suzhi was the father-in-law of Wang(2) Gui's [1845] nephew, Wang(2) Zhongkan [3943]. Since Suzhi, and his younger brother, Minzhi [19151], were both buried in Puxian, I am assigning their address to Puzhou where their father, Xun(5) [19150], must have remained. XCB, 181.11b, 182.3b-4a, 13b, 183.11a, 206.1a, 215.9b, 217.10b, 221.7a, 435.14b; SHY:ZG, 65.15a; SHY:SH, 56.16a; SS, 310.6b-7b; Sima Guang, WJ, 75.2b-3a; Su Song, WJ, 61.1a-8b. CBD, 2, 1034.</note>
